Today I am really feeling the artist block and frustration. It’s inevitable with the pace I am going at on my YouTube channel. How to come up with 3 videos a week along with my Patreon and keep it fresh & exciting. I had to scrap the video I was going to put out today because I wasn’t happy with it, and the funny thing is it was the second one I did, and I still wasn’t happy. So rather than put out crappy content I just didn’t. It really bothers me because I know why I have been feeling less creative. It’s because I am not creating anything for myself and my other clients. This has always been a dance but now it feels like sprint.

I am tossing around ideas to get myself back into a better creative flow rather than painting for painting sake. We are human and should expect to have burnout and block time to time. 

I also think people who support creators on these platforms should know how much energy and effort goes into every post and video.
There is the idea, the execution and then the editing, uploading and filling in the behind the scenes content. 

Lastly most ppl do not start channel’s because of the vulnerability it can become - you open yourself up to tons of criticism and comments that might baffle even the toughest person. So if you love a creator please please let them know this. A little goes a long way! I get my fair share of complaints that make me shake my head - but all my years living in NYC has made my skin thick - not everyone is molded this way. 

This painting was one of the last ones I did for “me” I can feel it’s love ❤️ & energy and this is why I need to do more for “me” . If you’re a creator spreading your talents to the world remember to take care of yourself- it’s the best way to stay connected to your art.
